parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the belt to unlatch during a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to the occupants.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle unlatches on its own
the buckle does not stay locked in place
the red release button is cracked
the seat belt will unbuckle by itself.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Service-Related Issues with Seat Belt Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper repair by the dealership during a seat belt recall can cause electrical problems, which can lead to other safety issues or malfunctions.
symptoms: Electrical problems after a seat belt recall repair
pierced electrical wire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended acceleration of the vehicle, combined with the failure of the brake system, can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
the engine revs loudly
the brakes do not respond or have a delayed response
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive wear of brake rotors can lead to a loss of braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake rotors wear out excessively
the brake pads wear out prematurely
the vehicle requires frequent brake repairs
the brakes make unusual noises or vibrate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear of front brake pads can lead to a loss of braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The front brake pads wear out prematurely
the vehicle requires frequent brake repairs
the brakes make unusual noises or vibrate
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration upon shifting can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates suddenly upon shifting from park to drive
resulting in unexpected and uncontrolled acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Differential pin failure can cause total loss of transmission function, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle will not shift out of 1st gear
transmission failure
sudden loss of power
and inability to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as well as leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle will not shift out of 1st gear
transmission failure
sudden loss of power
and inability to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and rusting of fuel lines can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
fuel smell
fuel dripping from the fuel lines
rust or corrosion visible on the fuel lines
decreased fuel efficiency
engine stalling or difficulty starting.
